I think we can do something like:

```scala
   val fromSemanticdb =
      semanticdbs.textDocument(path).documentIncludingStale
    val fromSnapshot = fromSemanticdb match {
      case Some(doc) =>
        definitionFromSnapshot(path, params, doc)
      case _ =>
        DefinitionResult.empty
    }
    val fromIndex =
      if (fromSnapshot.locations.isEmpty() && remote.isEnabledForPath(path)) {
          remote.definition(params).map(_.getOrElse(fromSnapshot))
      } else {
         fromSnapshot
        }
      } 
    if (fromIndex.locations.isEmpty()) {
      compilers().definition(params, token)
    } else {
      if(fromIndex.isEmpty)  warnings.noSemanticdb(path)
      Future.successful(fromIndex)
    }
```

This way it will also work for rambo mode, otherwise we assume that anything outside the build targets doesn't need any kind of compiler.

